The paper proposes a new method for perceptual grouping in visual scenes using spatial mixture models with learnable priors. This involves the use of neural networks to model the shape and appearance of objects separately, which suggests a focus on computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of mixture models and probability distributions also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper involves natural language processing (cs.CL) in its use of technical language and terminology.
